<L>__{interior kate's mother's home living room day}
<A>__{kate and charlie sit down. the place is a mess. magazines and junkmail everywhere. too much furniture thrown together in a chaotic manner. the walls are covered with framed heavy metal band posters and there are ashtrays everywhere, filled to the brim with cigarette butts.}
<C>__{rochelle }
<D>__{...you wouldn't believe how much the neighborhood's changed! after mr. baker passed away and the kids put mrs. baker in a home, the people that moved in, oof!}
<A>__{rochelle walks in holding a tray with three gin and tonics.}
<C>__{rochelle }
<D>__{it's like they don't even understand the concept of birth control in their country!}
<A>__{rochelle hands charlie a glass and then goes to kate and puts a drink on the table in front of her.}
<C>__{rochelle }
<P>__{(confides)}
<D>__{if you ask me, i think it's a meth house.}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{they've always got those little five year old twins "playing" in the yard, but i'm pretty sure they're the lookouts.}
